kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IPS_FORWARDING
kpi_info.use: The indication of whether this entity is acting as an IP router in respect to the forwarding of datagrams received by, but not addressed to, this entity. IP routers forward datagrams. IP hosts do not (except those source-routed via the host).

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IPS_DEFAULTTTL
kpi_info.use: The default value inserted into the Time-To-Live field of the IP header of datagrams originated at this entity, whenever a TTL value is not supplied by the transport layer protocol.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IPS_REASMTIMEOUT
kpi_info.use: The maximum number of seconds which received fragments are held while they are awaiting reassembly at this entity.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IPS_REASMREQDS
kpi_info.use: The number of IP fragments received which needed to be reassembled at this entity.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IPS_REASMFAILS
kpi_info.use: The number of failures detected by the IP re-assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc).

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IPS_INADDRERRORS
kpi_info.use: The number of input datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (e.g., Class E). For entities which are not IP routers and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_ICPS_INMSGS
kpi_info.use: The total number of ICMP messages which the entity received. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpInErrors.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_ICPS_OUTMSGS
kpi_info.use: The total number of ICMP messages which this entity attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpOutErrors.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_ICPS_OUTECHOREPS
kpi_info.use: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages sent.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_TCPS_INERRS
kpi_info.use: The total number of segments received in error (e.g., bad TCP checksums).

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_TCPS_OUTRSTS
kpi_info.use: The number of TCP segments sent containing the RST flag.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IP6S_INTOOBIGERRORS
kpi_info.use: The number of input datagrams that could not be forwarded because their size exceeded the link MTU of outgoing interface.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IP6S_INMCASTPKTS
kpi_info.use: The number of multicast packets received by the interface

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IP6S_OUTMCASTPKTS
kpi_info.use: The number of multicast packets transmitted by the interface

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IP6S_REASMTIMEOUT
kpi_info.use: The maximum number of seconds which received fragments are held while they are awaiting reassembly at this entity.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IP6S_REASMREQDS
kpi_info.use: The number of IP fragments received which needed to be reassembled at this entity.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IP6S_OUTREQUESTS
kpi_info.use: The total number of IP datagrams which local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_IP6S_INHDRERRORS
kpi_info.use: The number of input datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_ICP6S_INMSGS
kpi_info.use: The total number of ICMP messages received by the interface which includes all those counted by ipv6IfIcmpInErrors. Note that this interface is the interface to which the ICMP messages were addressed which may not be necessarily the input interface for the messages.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_ICP6S_OUTGMEMBRESPONSES
kpi_info.use: The number of ICMPv6 Group Membership Response messages sent.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_ICP6S_OUTGMEMBREDUCTIONS
kpi_info.use: The number of ICMPv6 Group Membership Reduction

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_ICP6S_OUTMSGS
kpi_info.use: The total number of ICMP messages which this interface attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpOutErrors.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_CURRESTAB
kpi_info.use: The number of associations for which the current state is either ESTABLISHED, SHUTDOWN-RECEIVED or SHUTDOWN-PENDING.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_ACTIVEESTABS
kpi_info.use: The number of times that associations have made a direct transition to the ESTABLISHED state from the COOKIE-ECHOED state: COOKIE-ECHOED -> ESTABLISHED. The upper layer initiated the association attempt.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_PASSIVEESTABS
kpi_info.use: The number of times that associations have made a direct transition to the ESTABLISHED state from the CLOSED state: CLOSED -> ESTABLISHED. The remote endpoint initiated the association attempt.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_ABORTEDS
kpi_info.use: The number of times that associations have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from any state using the primitive 'ABORT': AnyState --Abort--> CLOSED. Ungraceful termination of the association.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_SHUTDOWNS
kpi_info.use: The number of times that associations have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the SHUTDOWN-SENT state or the SHUTDOWN-ACK-SENT state. Graceful termination of the association.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_OUTOFBLUES
kpi_info.use: The number of out of the blue packets received by the host. An out of the blue packet is an SCTP packet correctly formed, including the proper checksum, but for which the receiver was unable to identify an appropriate association.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_CHECKSUMERRORS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP packets received with an invalid checksum.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_OUTCTRLCHUNKS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP control chunks sent (retransmissions are not included). Control chunks are those chunks different from DATA.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_OUTORDERCHUNKS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP ordered data chunks sent (retransmissions are not included).

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_OUTUNORDERCHUNKS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP unordered chunks (data chunks in which the U bit is set to 1) sent (retransmissions are not included).

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_INCTRLCHUNKS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP control chunks received (no duplicate chunks included).

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_INORDERCHUNKS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP ordered data chunks received (no duplicate chunks included).

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_INUNORDERCHUNKS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP unordered chunks (data chunks in which the U bit is set to 1) received (no duplicate chunks included).

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_FRAGUSRMSGS
kpi_info.use: The number of user messages that have to be fragmented because of the MTU.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_REASMUSRMSGS
kpi_info.use: The number of user messages reassembled, after conversion into DATA chunks.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_OUTSCTPPACKS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP packets sent. Retransmitted DATA chunks are included.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_INSCTPPACKS
kpi_info.use: The number of SCTP packets received. Duplicates are included.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_T1INITEXPIREDS
kpi_info.use: the number of association establishment failing because T1 timer expired after sending an INIT chunk but not receiving the acknowledgement

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_T1COOKIEEXPIREDS
kpi_info.use: the number of association establishment failing because T1 timer expired after sending a COOKIE-ECHO chunk but not receiving the acknowledge.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_T2SHUTDOWNEXPIREDS
kpi_info.use: the number of association establishment failing because T2 timer expired after sending a SHUTDOWN or SHUTDOWN-ACK chunk but not receiving the acknowledge.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_T3RTXEXPIREDS
kpi_info.use: When T3-rtx expires, the DATA chunks that triggered the T3 timer will be re-sent according with the retransmissions rules. Every DATA chunk that was included in the SCTP packet that triggered the T3-rtx timer must be added to the value of this counter.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_T4RTOEXPIREDS
kpi_info.use: the number of retransmit time out when T4 expired,included by SctpT3RtxExpireds.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_T5SDGUARDEXPIREDS
kpi_info.use: the number of association T5-shutdown-guard timer expired after sending SHUTDOWN-SENT state.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_DELAYSACKEXPIREDS
kpi_info.use: The number of delay selective acknowledge timer expired.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_AUTOCLOSEEXPIREDS
kpi_info.use: The number of association closed atuomatically when the peer endpoint is unreachable.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_T3RETRANSMITS
kpi_info.use: the times of retransmittion when T3 timer trigered.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_PMTUDRETRANSMITS
kpi_info.use: the retransmittion number of PMTU association.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_FASTRETRANSMITS
kpi_info.use: the retransmittion number with fast algorithm.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_INPKTSOFTIRQ
kpi_info.use: the softirq number of received packets.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_INPKTBACKLOG
kpi_info.use: the backlog number of received packets.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_INPKTDISCARDS
kpi_info.use: the discarded number of received packets.

kpi_info.title: TCPIP_SCTP_INDATACHUNKDISCARDS
kpi_info.use: the number of diecarded data chunks in the received packets.
